@dset0x Thanks for this massive work :+1: 

I saw you added `version: post-release version bump`, this is usually done after release. For the release you could set it to `2.0.0` if we agree on this being a major version (which makes sense).

However, the version is usually changed in the "release commit", typically generated by repository owners. See e.g. https://github.com/inveniosoftware/invenio-records/commit/ad47c637486e231323c4d01e9c238f6a85cf2cf4

