Could you run `systemctl cat deis-publisher` on one of your CoreOS hosts? That would confirm for sure that you're using the older unit. The new one should look like this: https://github.com/deis/deis/blob/master/deisctl/units/deis-publisher.service

I'm betting that once we fix #3832 and build a new `deisctl`, that installing that and installing the new publisher unit would get you running on v1.7 just fine...

