I don't think implementing static (aka persisted) queries is within the scope of the Graphene project since it is tightly coupled to the rest of your application. You would need to define where the persisted queries are stored, how the front end part of your app adds new queries, how your server interprets static queries etc.

Here is a quick pseudo code example of how I imagine it could be setup inside an application:

```python
// Graphql endpoint view
import graphene

from my_graphql_server import schema // your apps schema

def graphql_endpoint(request):
	query_identifier, variables = parse_body(request)

	try:
		// Retrieve a grapqhl.language.ast.Document instance from an identifier
		// so that query doesn't need to be parsed again
		document = get_document_from_identifier(query_identifier)
		return schema.execute(document, variable_values=variables)
	except QueryNotFound:
		return HttpResponse(status=404) 
```

